caption: Kyle
Excellent service and food....
Cool place. Loved the atmosphere.  Games outside to play, great staff, good food.

The food was good. Everyone of us enjoyed our order. We got 4 different sandwiches and an app to share, the table was silent the entire time. The menu is small but the drinks are decently priced. Its basically small bites and sandwiches. There's open bartop tables and a seated patio area. I saw a small area with cornhole boards and a few other items. There are also board games for people who sit inside. I gave it three stars because our server was horrible. I've been in the industry for years and her attentiveness needs some work. You should NEVER neglect one of your tables while deeply conversing with the one behind it. Maybe if we had a different server my experience would have been better. The food runner ended up being the highlight of my evening. He was super friendly every time he came out. I'll try again next time we are in town with a different server.

we tried MAC 'N EGG ROLL as an appetizer which we ordered just because it sounded crazy. it's mac and cheese in an egg roll. They were pretty good. The dipping sauce was the best part in my opinion. Probably wouldn't order again but i'm glad we tried them. I got the ole smokey and it was pretty good. overall I left happy with no complaints.
Quality food, great service and friendly people

Melt is pretty consistent in their food. I’ve been many times and will continue to go back many more. The staff is friendly and the atmosphere is always great! The drinks change depending on who me asked them, but they are still usually pretty good! The last time is went was the Saturday before St. Patrick’s Day, they were slammed, but were still had great service! Give it a try.
Excellent service and delicious food! We sat outside on Sat.March 13,2021 & had live 🎶 music, ...just delightful. Moderate prices, and a fun atmosphere.!
This place never disappoints! Food is always amazing and they always have drink specials  Their sandwiches are on point but today I got the wedge salad with grilled chicken . It was huge and perfect
Fast service, good food and atmosphere.
Such wonderful food and great atmosphere. We will definitely be visiting again.

Love every opportunity to take someone new their. The atmosphere is great and the service is wonderful. Your meal is always that much better when the workers all seem to be happy & enjoying their job. We absolutely love going there and the food is so yummy. If you like something with a little twist on some of the old time favorites like a grilled cheese sandwich etc. you won’t be disappointed . Definitely make it one of your go to places.
The cuban was great!
Food, atmosphere, and service make this place special. I love it here although it is somewhat pricey for me. Highly recommend.
Good food, awesome customer service

Pretty good! The mac'n'egg roll was so unique! I got the reuben (because if there is ever an option to get one, that's my go-to). The reuben was good, but not the most amazing one I have ever had. It's a trendy place, conveniently located downtown. Seems like they usually stay pretty busy!
The bar is great as well as food.

Decided to try something different for my birthday so went here. Overall, the food was pretty good. I got the patty melt which I would recommend asking for Mayo or some type of sauce so it isn’t so dry. We tried the Mac N’ egg roll appetizer which was good. The staff was very friendly and service was pretty quick. I didn’t rate 5 stars because I felt it was overpriced. We paid around $90 for 2 kids meals and 3 sandwich meals.

Best brunch in Huntsville by far. $3 mimosas is tough to beat, but the food takes the cake. If you're familiar with the SoCal brunch scene, MELT is as close as you're going to get to Breakfast Republic without having to wait 90 minutes for a table.
Absolutely delicious

We ordered our drinks and entrees. The food was served quickly and professionally. The portion sizes tended to be on the small size. The food was quite bland, not tasteless, but also not memorable. The prices were high. Overall, everything is amazing. Highly recommended.
Tricked me into double tipping the waiter.  Food was very good. If you add 18% gratuity , tell us. The email that you asked me to message you in isn’t a valid email🤔

My husband has been trying to get me here since it opened, and I finally had the opportunity today. I ordered the Mac Melt and it was awesome! What is really driving me to leave a review was the Kid's Quesadilla. Whoever made the kid's menu is obviously a parent. This was really a child sized portion of literally just cheese on a tortilla. We chose fries as her side, and to my surprise it came not only with fries but also with Goldfish crackers! In 2 years of ordering a kid's meal, this is the first time someone realized that kids don't care for finely seasoned sides and just want a handful of Goldfish. The atmosphere is definitely relaxing. Our waitress was amazingly attentive. I hear pre-covid that they have board games available to play at your table. There is also an awesome out door area with huge games to play like big connect4, ladder ball, corn hole, and scrabble. 10/10 will go again and again!

Great sandwiches and a cool atmosphere. You can also walk up to the bar from the outside if you need a quick drink. Dishes come out very fast so you won’t have to wait long for your food. Will be back!

While the service was impeccable (earning them their stars) the food was extremely underwhelming. We ordered the Food Truck Nachos and we really couldn’t tel you anything more than the super sweet bbq sauce was all you could taste. The toppings were all clumped together so you had dry chips and then chips that were soggy. There was so much bbq sauce and it is so sweet that you couldn’t taste anything else. We also ordered the baked goat cheese and it was ok but lacked any depth of flavor, again being overly sweet with nothing but honey, goat cheese, crasins and pecans.  My husband had one of the sandwiches and it was ok, again just nothing special. With so many amazing restaurants to choose from we likely won’t choose Melt again unless the menu gets an overhaul and they develop some better flavors.
Wonderful brunch and even better service! Make sure you try the Mac and cheese eggroll. You won't be disappointed.

Food was great! First time here and will definitely be back! My 9 year old had the Mac Melt and said it's the best sandwich she's ever had. My chicken parm sandwich was the bomb as well. The fried Oreo is a secret treasure and I love to introduce it to new people. highly recommend this place
Everything was great!
Food was amazing. Very nice place with outside seating even available at the bar. Looking forward to trying some other dishes.
We enjoyed every bite. Kids loved outdoor games. Even dog approved!
Flying Hawaiian. That's all you need to try there. 10/10
Donny is the best. He always makes sure our meal is perfect. We always look forward to our visit to MELT.

Enjoyed myself with some good friends, good drinks, and good food. I split a Reuben and a Cuban, they were both good but they're  different sandwiches; not really in the same ball park for comparisons.
Our sandwiches
Overall good experience. Service was quick,  food was good,  and staff was nice.  I'll most definitely be back.
Food was excellent and service was great. We will definitely be back. (Save room for the deep fried Oreos)
Love this place
Awesome service and food, just expensive
The food and staff were amazing! We are definitely going back
A must eat. The food is absolutely amazing and the price is a steal for how good the food is. And on a plus the staff are nice and friendly.
Great Great food Great people.

Great food, Great service, Great night!  My family some friends and I went here for dinner one night, and got an awesome experience. Food was fresh and tasted great, and was very clean and well maintained! All in all, would recommend this to anyone who is looking for somewhere to eat in the Downtown Huntsville area.
This place slaps! The sandwiches are delicious

Ooooo, so yummy! Loaded and tasty. We started with a Santa's Helper drink. Then we went crazy and enjoyed Fried Pickles and Mac and Choose Eggrolls for appetizers; the Ol' Smoky, Patty Melt and the 3 Amigos for the main meal; and the Fried Double Stuff Oreos and Banana Stand for dessert. Wow! Great staff, great food!
Very nice!
Great service and appetizers!
Love the Chicken Pesto sandwich!
The service is always nice, and the burgers are delicious. Each burger is served on texas toast or a normal bun.
Food and service were both great
Nice to be able to eat outside.  Service was meh but the food was good.  Beer selection is rife with local selections and the seating outside is roomy and felt safe.
This place just deserves 5 stars. The Mac n Roll was just unbelievable!
This place is the best. Everything is delicious. Highly recommended.
Love it! Everything we had was delicious! The mac n cheese rolls. Yep! Better grab it.
Great seating area outside. Good choices on the menu. Friendly staff.
Food was great and our server, Kyle was fantastic. He suggested things and got all 5 of us to try the fried oreos. They were delicious.
Great restaurant! This was my family's first time eating here.
Raging Cajun sandwich was amazing!! Seasoned perfectly. Not too little, not too much. Chicken was cooked perfectly too. Not dry at all and just fell apart when you bit into the sandwich. Super yummy!
Excellent food!
Some of the best food I've had.  Staff was friendly and the food arrived in a timely manner.  I highly recommend the mac-and-cheese egg rolls.
Underrated. Great place, great service, great food.
Not a good place to go if you’re not white lol. They do not make you feel welcome at all and act extremely nervous or rude.
Friends said to try it out. Was not disappointed.
Food was good, portion size nice and good friendly staff
Love the grilled buffalo chicken sandwich!

Server was very inattentive, food served with no napkins or silverware. Food was decent, but small servings for the price. Was a bit too pretentious for me...rosemary ketchup was just plain gross, and whoever's made the bleu cheese should be strung up...it is a disgrace  to even call it bleu cheese, didn't taste good at all!!
Great service and food was wonderful. Try the fried oreos. They are amazing!
Great service and dog friendly

Saturday evening with the sun going down, music starting on the patio and groups of family/friends coming in --  we could still have a conversation and were checked on regularly by server.  The atmosphere and food were wonderful and the staff was gracious. Enjoyed the "Falling for You" salad with grilled chicken. Salad had superb flavor, and the grilled chicken was outstanding.  Kudos to the chef and manager.
Cool concept but basic.
Was great food, had outdoor seating which was a bonus for us. Friendly servers here

They advertise that they’re following COVID protocols and that their tables are distanced 6 ft apart, but they definitely not. Servers are barely wearing their masks and offer extremely poor service. Food is mediocre. Don’t waste your time with this place.
Food was really good, friendly staff and nice atmosphere, did have to wait a little longer for our waiter than we wanted a couple times but that didn't ruin our experience.
Great experience.  Great food. Manger was engaged  with his customers.  FOOD WAS OUT FAST.
Different type of food than ur normal restaurant. But was pretty good
Not pretentious like some the restaurants in that area. Great service and the sandwiches are hearty.
Very nice restaurant with great food and drink choices, along with a very friendly staff. Quick and efficient service every time I visit.
Nice patio to dine outdoors. Great food and service.

Sandwiches are great! Service (waiters) could improve, especially when the restaurant isn't busy: after lunch before dinner. Thank you for the social distancing, wearing masks as servers, & maintaining a clean eating area.
Great service, mimosas and brunch!

The girl that served our food  last night didnt have her mask over her nose. It made us disgusted and concerned.  Management needs to brush up on how sickness spreads and enforce employees wearing masks correctly... It's not optional even though everyone is tired of doing it.
Kyle was a great server! Food was amazing! Highly recommend!
Kyle was an excellent server and we thoroughly enjoyed our meal

Wow! I was pleasantly surprised by my excellent experience at this Melt location. I’m from Birmingham and I’ve never been to the location there, but I was meeting a friend in Huntsville and we decided to try it. Our food was delicious (especially fried Oreos for dessert!). In particular, our server Kyle made the experience memorable and fun. Definitely coming back!
Food was SO delicious!! One of my first meals out since Covid and I felt very safe (sat outside). Our server, Kyle, was hilarious and took great care of us.
Awesome atmosphere! Our food was out almost immediately, our server was nice and helpful, and the food was delicious. Will definitely be going back for more!
Good food just as pictured! Will go again!
Great place, service was really good and the food was even better. The best french fries I have ever had!
Took 15 minutes for a server to show up, when she finally did, this was the glass of rose that was delivered after an additional 10 minutes. Cool. Cool, cool, cool.
Kyle was a really good server! Gave us the best service

This eatery was very good and the food tasted great. I had a raging Cajun and it was excellent.  Their beer battered fries were amazing. Jessica out server was very good and very sweet. Their deep fried Oreos were very good. The outside seating was well arranged and very pleasant. I would return here for sure.
Great service and excellent atmosphere
Great place! Friendly service, excellent design, and delishous food.
Great food

Ally was an amazing server! I will always request her in the future! Very sweet, patient, and energetic! Keep up the good work! Food was amazing and fresh going back tomorrow. This was my first visit and I was not disappointed!
Love Melt! Great food, nice and courteous staff. One of my favs... Chicken pesto sandwich!
Fantastic cuban/midnight sandwich.

Big shout out to Kyle!  He was the icing on the cake of our meal at The Melt!  What a wonderful young man!  In addition, Shelby was on top of it all!  The Melt is lucky to have these two!!!  We will be back, hope we get to see them again!!❤️
Great food.. Lovely staff.. Recommended
The service here is awesome. The employees are very friendly and helpful. The food was very good, just a little expensive. It's a cool experience to eat here!

I enjoyed the atmosphere it would be pretty cool if they offered mask for anyone who forgot one....really enjoyed their beyond burger everything on it went together so well & the fried oreos were so fulfilling i wouldn't mind eating here again..should definitely see about getting cauliflower bites or other vegan options put on the menu tho

Wooow this place is amazing. The food was so great. The service was even better. One of the best experiences I’ve had at a restaurant. The hostess was sooo sweet & our server was just the BEST ❤️ I believe her name is Traci. Thank you so much!! Definitely check this place out!
Great place to grab a quick bite, dog friendly!
Great downtown atmosphere will be going back for sure!
Great salads and flat  bread My first visit but not my last
Awesome first date with my wife since the pandemic started. We feel so comfortable with the way Melt handled social distancing. Each table in the street was around 15 ft. apart from each other.
Wow! Really awesome and everything was great...  service, food, desert, etc... A MUST in Huntsville!
I must have this place every time I visit! It has been spot on every single time. Great food, staff and atmosphere - Love It!!
Have gone twice and both times were good.
Adult Capri suns!  Need I say more??
Outdoor seating, good food quick. Friendly staff
Awesome patty melt
Love their food!
Great designer food and craft beer.. Good service
Excellent food and service, virus controls working well
Good food and great choices on the menu.
Excellent service and meal.
My bad, I underrated Melt. Went there with my son that just moved to Huntsville. He suggested we go to Melt. So glad we did, it was delicious! Def recommend and we will be back!

Highly recommend!! Shortly before I arrived a group of 70 came in.  So I expected some sort of wait.  To my surprise the wait to be seated only took less than a min.  10 min after I was seated, my food arrived.  Big props to the employees, no one seemed overwhelmed and everyone seemed very professional.  Its in a great location! The facility were clean.  The food, was amazing! I will most definitely be coming back.
Great food and service- their pimento cheese is incredible, as well as the goat cheese appetizer.  Fun, kid-friendly atmosphere without being obnoxious about it.  My whole family loves going here.
Great food, great service. Clean and very accommodating for current restrictions due to pandemic.

Great sandwich place. Very nice employees. The only little annoying thing was that you had to look up the menu online. They did have a paper brunch menu. Everyone liked their sandwich. It was nice that they have a vegan burger. (Our daughter is vegan)
Good service, good food
The Cuban Sub is a favorite!
The food was fresh . Service was fast.
Awesome food and great atmosphere.   Prices are reasonable
Great food
Melt has the most amazing sandwiches around. The wait staff was awesome. Definitely recommend stopping by lunch or dinner.
Great experience and food!!
Stopped in for a quick lunch. Cool place! We'll be back!
Great Patty Melt, fun drinks, great service. Was able to eat outside and away from others, all the employees were wearing masks.
It was okay but over priced

Some friends and I tried this restaurant for the first time today. We sat down at approximately 12:10 and didn't get food until after 12:45. Others who came in after us got their food first. Our waitress checked on us twice. When we got the food, my order was wrong and it was cool (assuming it had been sitting). The service was barely mediocre. I'm extremely disappointed and dissatisfied. My expectations were greater. I feel we were looked over and am very unhappy. This is highly unacceptable.

Some friends and I tried this restaurant for the first time today. We sat down at approximately 12:10 and didn't get food until after 12:45. Others who came in after us got their food first. Our waitress checked on us twice. When we got the food, my order was wrong and it was cool (assuming it had been sitting). The service was mediocre at best. I'm extremely disappointed and dissatisfied. My expectations were greater. I feel we were looked over and am very unhappy.
Never a disappointment. Turned my TN family friends onto the Melt.  Had to peel them away...4 different entrees all good.
Good! But a little pricey
Delicious food, good cocktails. Dining room open.
Erica (like America) was amazing. Honestly would come back just to hang out with her. The food was also great which was a plus.

The people are amazing. Donnie the manager has been wonderful.  Always welcoming on every occation. He is surrounded by a great staff and Ashley the bartender is amazing 👏.  Super friendly and so much fun. The kind of energy you want behind the bar. Will be coming back for more
Donnie and staff are great....food is well prepared with large portions... Recommend
I was here for a cheer competition and I decided to bring a few friends here with me and it was so good! The scenery inside and out it amazing!
Just a fun place to go. Great bar too.
Awesome food 👍 we will definitely order again!!
The atmosphere is great at this location, and the grilled Mac n cheese is very good.

We dined in with another family and the wait staff accommodated us with no issues having a kids table and an adult table. I ate the chicken pesto sandwich and it was very good. The rest of the adults ordered the meatloaf and they absolutely raved about it.
Went to Melt today for St. Patrick’s Day , Ashley the bartender was awesome . If you guys get out and need a great a drink she definitely one of the best bartenders around .

Went to Melt for lunch and the staff was courteous. The atmosphere is relaxed but modern. I ordered the 3 Amigos and it was good but could have used abit more cheese. Overall great place and would happily come back if I came to Huntsville again.

Great location I always enjoy myself when I'm here. I love that they have an indoor outdoor bar which you don't see often which makes it an excellent place to dine. They're also activities for kids and adults which makes it a fun atmosphere. I would highly recommend trying it out !

This place is just truly amazing. I have been multiple times before and have never been disappointed. I have tried many things and they have all been good. All I can say if you go, be sure to try the fried pickles because they are amazing!
Very clean and nice place to eat.

MELT is a 5 star establishment, they have delicious food and you can really tell they put their all into it. I have had great experiences everytime I've visited this place. Tyler the bartender, is amazing at making you a drink you enjoy. The server Shelby helped me pick out something delicious to eat. And I even had a splendid conversation with another server, CJ.
Ok ..very fatty

Had Melt for the first time today, and it was the best restaurant experience my husband and I have had in a long time. Friendly and helpful staff!! Ouu waitress, Brooklyn, was THE BEST and sweetest! We will definitely be back! P.s. try the goat cheese 😁

I'm not the biggest cheese fan (I do like it, but not obsessively), so I'd say that food wise, the cheese is a bit much. Delicious, but very cheesy.  Be ready for ALL the cheese.  Their fried pickles were good too. My favorite part was definitely the board games they have laying around to play.  It made me nostalgic.

This review is to praise Kyle! He was the host the night my family & I dined here. He was cheerful, friendly, & helpful from the moment we walked in (despite our party of 9). He gave us dinner recommendations & went out of his way to make sure we were comfortable in the booth we were given. Excellent customer service. The food was delicious, as well! Would return if ever in Huntsville again:)
Loved the menu variety and recommend the goat cheese app!
Enjoyed myself both times!
Portions too small but great taste!
Tyler was the BEST server ever! Whenever I go there I am very pleased with my service.
Great food, hands down!
Fried pickles are a force to be reckoned with

We had a fantastic evening at Melt. We ate outside on the patio with our two dogs. Everyone was very welcoming, and the attention to service went above and beyond. Thank you Melt for giving us a place we can eat together as a family. 🐕🐾
Good food, prices are a little high, but it is a downtown location. Good service.
Food was average, service was great.
Great service and nifty menu. Enjoyed the experience and the food.
Really good food and excellent service. Menu seems very diverse with a good selection. Can’t wait to try more of what they have to offer.

My food was very tasty oh, I also got an Irish mule it was really good definitely recommend that. My serving of fries was rather small, and I was still hungry after eating. Which hardly ever happens. It also said it was out-of-this-world spicy I know I really like spicy things, but this was not spicy at all. It was still good however. My friend ordered a Cuban and even ask for a recommendation to see if it was good or not and she hardly had any meat on her sandwich. The customer at the next table ordered the same thing in his had a lot of me on it and he was even pushing it back in with a fork. My server Breanna was very nice and polite. I probably won't come back because I spent $12 on a Ragin Cajun which didn't even fill me up.

All I can say is if you haven't tried this place stop what you're doing and go right now!!! I've passed several times and never stopped so today me and my coworkers all decided we would go, and let me tell you it was the best decision we've made.  Food was excellent, large portions and a very fair price. We kept passing around samples of each others food we were all so impressed.  Only downside was I wanted to try all the other sandwiches after but I'll just have to come back

Terrific spot. Local brews & Specialty Drinks. Food is fantastic with vegan options. Tyler's service exceeded expectations and the GM did well to ensure our satisfaction.  Also the best $3 dessert in town, the fried Oreos.
The service is amazing.  The ambiance was perfect.  The brunch menu is fantastic!
VERY good food, came very fast! We were served by a very seeet girl named Brooklyn !

For a place called Melt, there wasn't much melty goodness to be had with what we ordered. I had the Flyin Hawaiian with Tomato Basil Soup and my fiance had the Reuben with fries. We also ordered the Mac & Egg roll, which, along with my lemonade and our server, Brooklyn, was the only positive about the experience. My sandwich barely had any cheese to speak of and it was only moderately warm. The soup was edible but nothing I'd return for and almost any canned tomato soup would put it to shame, which is...a shame. My fiance's sandwich had a criminally tiny portion of sauerkraut but decent flavor. We enjoyed our appetizer, our server was attentive and warm, and I could drink gallons of the Lemonade, but all in all, this was a disappointing experience.

First time in today during lunch on a Friday. Brooklyn (sp?) was a spectacular waitress with a couple great suggestions to edit their menu items. We had the Food Truck Nachos...but substituted fries....slam dunk! I had the Ole' Smokey sandwich with a pretzel bun instead of the local sourdough bun....another slam dunk! Atmosphere is great. Staff seemed very attentive and the orders came out in a very reasonable time, especially during lunch rush on a Friday. Melt will definitely get a spot in the normal rotation of the wife and I's hangout joints in HSV!!

First time visitor to this place with my wife on valentine's day. We LOVED it. Great atmosphere, our waitress was super helpful and honestly answered our questions and the food was fantastic. Highly recommend for a quick lunch or dinner.

Was in town for work & hit this place with my colleagues. Had the nachos & the Cuban. Tyler was our server. The food, atmosphere, decor, & service are STELLAR. Thanks for a great night, Melt! And give Tyler a raise! 😂
Great twist on your favorite sandwich shop. Local craft beers and a neat atmosphere.

It was my first time at Melt. I usually don't go downtown. Erica like America is very attentive to detail and hospitable. However my raging Cajun sandwich was not spicy at all. I'm grateful the service made up for the lack of flavor in my sandwich. I will definitely return to see Erica again.
Friendly people. Good quality food.
Good food with a neat atmosphere. Friendly staff. If you like Justin Timberlake, you'll love the music, haha! I think half the songs were JT.

First visit..food was good, service was good except we had to wait on our drinks a bit...they had only been open 45min... atmosphere was nice, they have board games and outside games for adults and kids..
Jason work the bar was very helpful and awesome great customer service!!!
The sandwiches here are fantastic. Friendly staff and patrons.
Great food and Amazing Deserts...
Love This place with their unique menu items. I look forward to our next visit.

I was unfortunately disappointed with our visit to melt. The food was good and serving size was good I just wasnt blown away. The kids menu was in my opinion overpriced and I purposefully asked the waitress before ordering if kids meal included a drink to which she responded yes. We then got the bill and were charged almost 3 dollars for a lemonade...I brought it to her attention that I had asked her beforehand and she said it was included, her response was "I misunderstood what you asked" she then proceeded to not apologize and billed us for the drink. I also had to send back my water because the ice was dirty, there was no explanation or apology given for that either. The fries are delicious and they have the best housemade ranch I've ever had...I think from the 3 meals we ordered our sons chicken tenders were our favorite.
Very good food, drinks were unique, and that waiter Tim is a dreamboat😍
Loved both of our meals and we will b back.
Food was really good. Service was good. The goat cheese appetizer was amazing!
Went for a Facebook Christmas Event... It was awesome. Prices and parking wasn't great though.
Pretty cool place
Comfort food and an interesting outdoor hang.  The Ole Smokey sourdough is SO tasty also try the Buffalo chicken salad, great zing.  Friendly staff.

The cheeseburger was amazing! Tried a little bit of the Mac ’n’ Cheese grilled sandwich my friend was eating and wasn’t disappointed. Shoutout to Jerry, our server, for giving us great service! Definitely recommend and plan on coming back. ; )

It's ok. It was cool to try and the atmosphere is pretty nice with yard games and all. But based off just food and price it was pretty underwhelming. Go there for the unique items that you can't find anywhere else. If you go and get something like a basic burger or patty melt, you gonna leave a little disappointed because you spent what will feel like too much on something that you had somewhere else that was probably better and cheaper.
Yummy food good atmosphere
They have lots of cheese. Cheese is good af.
Casual dining with odd combinations of food that, strangely, work well
1st time and must go back! Service was great and my food and drinks were so delish!!
Grilled cheese lacked in flavor.

Was fantastic when it first opened, but the food and drink preparation have suffered. I had a chicken sandwich and it only had 1 tender on it. The fries weren't very good, and they seem to be out of items on the menu too often.

This was our first visit. The service was decent and the food tasted good, but three out of four of the sandwiches we got were fairly small and we each got very few fries (the cheeseburger my wife had was decent sized). Overall, I was disappointed.  The meal was very over-priced for what we got. I think the sandwiches would have been fairly priced at $6-$7 not the $12-$13 we paid.  I don't think we will go back.
Great place to eat and great service
Nice and casual spot in the heart of DT Huntsville.
Best Reuben in town
Food and staff were amazing!
Good service. Fair orices. Great food.
The Goat cheese app and the Mac and Cheese melt were amazing.  Perfect combo of flavors and textures.  We'll definitely be back.
Good food, nice cocktails and a good atmosphere.
Food is always great, service is good as well
Nice place. You could actually talk with out yelling
Food was really tasty. Fries could have been more fresh. Server was friendly.
Great food.
Man those beer battered fries!! Lexi was awesome 👍
Food was great once we finally got someone to take our order. Would give it a second shot.

My husband and I were passing through Huntsville trying to find a good place with American pub-like food for lunch. Melt did not disappoint. Absolutely amazing food, very reasonable prices, and the waitstaff was friendly and helpful. Cannot recommend enough.

First visit was a great one. Been looking forward to trying this place. Great selection on the menu. Fun atmosphere.  Family friendly. Games outside and fantastic music inside. Will definitely go back.  Great outside are as well as inside accommodations for large groups. Check this.one out soon. We tried the patt6 mely with kettle chips and the turkey club and tomato bisque soup. YUM!  The fun napkin holders are metal lunch boxes in case you cant tell feom the pic. What a great idea. Fun place.
First time to eat at the Melt. Really good food and nice atmosphere.
Fried pickles, turkey sandwich and Mac and cheese were all delicious.

Appetizer - mac & cheese egg roll = was the best out of everything. Entree - We had the 3 amigos and flying Hawaiian with fries. Was just ok. Dessert - fried oreos = way to much breading. Could hardly taste the Oreo! Not as good as I've heard it was. 😢
Great service, welcoming staff and great food.
Best service and food around. Reasonably priced. Not a bad thing on the menu. Children's meals come with fries and goldfish so our little one loved it. Try the fried Oreos.

My expectations for Melt in Huntsville were set by previous experiences at Melt restaurants in Ohio (Cleveland). Turns out this is a different Melt chain and an inferior one.  The experience was pleasant - it's located in downtown Huntsville, a short and enjoyable walk from our hotel. And there a number of indoor and outdoor games to play while we waited for our food - Jenga, ping-pong, ladder ball, etc.  However, the sandwiches were very underwhelming. The roll used for my sandwich was hard, and the sandwich itself generally lacked flavor. My wife was equally unsatisfied with her order as she did not care to finish.  While Melt gets good marks for experience and service, it gets poor marks for the food.

It's just OK, nothing more nothing less. The venue is located in new hip downtown apartment building. Could have been Soho Or Seattle. The interior of the restaurant is modern sleek very inviting and table service was crisp and well intentioned My problem is with the food and presentation. Pacing was also problematic  All ordered items came to the table rapid fire before the salad was 1/3 completed. My partner had a veggie burger which was just ok but lacked taste with the bun becoming  mushy because of  condiments, lettuce and tomato.A. quick fix could be a toasted French baguette to solve that problem. I had the Ragin Cajun sandwich  which was good but suffered the same fate as the burger.Texas toast will be a mushy mess with coleslaw  roasted pork and condiments. Apparently the restaurant doesn't have a sandwich press which might solve this  problem. The mac and cheese appetizer was very good They use paper napkins which I loath..They use small clear glasses that requires the server to constantly refill.Too much back and forth. Not great for the landfills either. All in all OK and waiting to be GREAT!

Simply the best sandwich shop in Huntsville, AL.  Attention to detail from bread to meat to sauces we haven't had a sandwich here that we didn't love.  Great food PLUS friendly hostesses who pass out board games to their guests and waiters who are on point!  Oh, and don't miss the deep fried Oreo's with powered sugar topping!

Came here for a Ragin Cajun sandwich with fries and a mac n cheese egg roll.  The sandwich was better than i expected. Its a spicy cajun style piece of grilled chicken served on toasted bread with coleslaw. The chicken was a little bit spicier than I anticipated but it was pleasantly offset by the fresh coleslaw topping. I thought using the toasted bread was a great choice since it gives the sandwich a good solid construction so you don't lose any of the coleslaw like you would on a roll or a bun.  The mac n cheese egg roll was delicious and it came with a sweet & spicy dipping sauce that was more spicy than sweet but it turned out to be a perfect compliment to the cajun sandwich.  The only thing i didn't love about this meal was the side of fries. They were a little bland and not crispy like you'd expect from beer battered fries.  All in all though, great meal, and I will definitely try more sandwiches in the future. Would love to see a Monte Cristo added to the menu as well!

This place is twice as big as the original restaurant in Birmingham. Thats a good thing and is the result of Melt’s success in Birmingham. Melt started as a food truck, and was so wildly popular, they were able to get finding for a restaurant. That restaurant is great, and the menu is the same in Birmingham and Huntsville. The problem with the Birmingham restaurant is that it’s too small.  The Huntsville restaurant is stylish and modern, well lit, with a fancy bar that can serve outside and inside. This is an improvement to the Birmingham restaurant, which was built on a much lower budget, and always has a line at lunch and dinner. This place is great and highly recommended.  The basic philosophy of the restaurant is built on the classic grilled cheese sandwich. Take that favorite and add various meats and other flavors. My personal favorite is the Flyin’ Hawaiian, which is ham and pineapple. The sandwiches are all great, and the mac and cheese is also very good. They serve various beers that I am not qualified to evaluate.
Service was excellent, got food quickly and it was very hot. Will definitely recommend to others and will return myself.

Just talk with him and he will make you a fantastic drink based on your likes if you can't decide on one of their drinks.  This is a must stop and try restaurant - you will not regret it!
